{
  "chapter": {
    "description": "A quick look at artificial intelligence before the course dives into the details. You'll see what AI actually does, where it already touches your daily life, some surprising ideas behind how it works, and the many paths people take once they start working with it. By the end, you'll have a feel for why this field is worth your time and what the rest of the course will help you build.",
    "title": "What artificial intelligence really is"
  },
  "lessons": [
    {
      "description": "AI isn't one single thing but a collection of techniques that let computers recognize patterns, make predictions, and generate new content. This lesson breaks down that broad label into simple, concrete terms so the word 'AI' stops feeling mysterious.",
      "title": "What people mean when they say 'AI'"
    },
    {
      "description": "From the playlist that predicts your next favorite song to the phone camera that finds faces in a crowd, AI already quietly shapes ordinary moments. This lesson points out everyday places AI is working behind the scenes, often without anyone noticing.",
      "title": "Where AI hides in your everyday life"
    },
    {
      "description": "A computer program taught itself to beat world champions at games no one programmed it to win by rules alone. This lesson shares that story as a window into how machines can find strategies humans never thought to try.",
      "title": "The surprising moment a machine outsmarted the experts"
    },
    {
      "description": "Some people build the models, others clean the data, test for fairness, write about AI, or apply it to medicine, art, and climate science. This lesson maps out the variety of roles and communities connected to AI work today.",
      "title": "Who works with AI, and what they actually do"
    },
    {
      "description": "This lesson previews how the full course is organized, from the core ideas that make AI systems tick to the hands-on skills for building and reasoning about them. It sets expectations for what's ahead and how the pieces fit together.",
      "title": "How this course will take you further"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "chapter": {
    "description": "Um passeio curto pelo mundo da vida antes de começar o curso de verdade. Aqui você vai sentir do que a Biologia trata: como células, corpos, espécies e ecossistemas funcionam, por que isso aparece na sua saúde, na comida que você come e nas decisões do planeta, e quais ideias tornam essa ciência surpreendentemente bonita. No fim, você vai entender por que vale a pena seguir em frente e o que o curso completo vai destrinchar peça por peça.",
    "title": "O que a Biologia estuda"
  },
  "lessons": [
    {
      "description": "Toda planta, fungo, bactéria ou animal compartilha características parecidas: são feitos de células, usam energia, crescem e se reproduzem. Essa lição mostra o fio condutor que une todos os seres vivos e por que os biólogos usam isso como ponto de partida.",
      "title": "O que todo ser vivo tem em comum"
    },
    {
      "description": "Seu corpo troca bilhões de células todos os dias sem que você perceba, e o DNA guarda instruções que conectam você a organismos de milhões de anos atrás. Uma ideia rápida e surpreendente sobre como a vida se renova e se conecta.",
      "title": "Uma ideia que muda como você vê seu próprio corpo"
    },
    {
      "description": "Da fermentação do pão à resistência de bactérias a remédios, passando pelo cuidado com plantas em casa: a Biologia aparece em decisões cotidianas de saúde, alimentação e meio ambiente sem que a gente sempre note.",
      "title": "A biologia escondida no seu dia a dia"
    },
    {
      "description": "Biólogos trabalham em laboratórios, florestas, hospitais, fazendas e até em jogos e games educativos. Um panorama leve de caminhos, projetos e comunidades que giram em torno do estudo da vida.",
      "title": "O que quem estuda vida faz na prática"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "chapter": {
    "description": "A quick tour of the strange, small-scale world that runs underneath everything you touch, see, and use. Before the equations and formal rules begin, this chapter shows what quantum mechanics actually studies, why it quietly powers modern life, and why physicists still find it startling. You'll see a few of its strangest ideas, meet the kinds of people who work with them, and get a sense of where the full course will take you next.",
    "title": "A First Look at the Quantum World"
  },
  "lessons": [
    {
      "description": "Quantum mechanics is the science of how matter and energy behave at the scale of atoms and particles, where the familiar rules of everyday objects stop working. This lesson gives a plain-language feel for what physicists are actually trying to describe down there.",
      "title": "What quantum mechanics is really about"
    },
    {
      "description": "A single particle can behave as if it takes many paths at once, only settling into one outcome when observed. This lesson introduces that puzzle in a simple, concrete way, without any math, just to show how odd the quantum world can be.",
      "title": "The strange idea of many possibilities at once"
    },
    {
      "description": "From the phone in your pocket to hospital scanners and GPS satellites, quantum effects are working behind the scenes. This lesson connects quantum ideas to devices and technologies you already rely on every day.",
      "title": "Where quantum physics hides in daily life"
    },
    {
      "description": "People who work with quantum mechanics build lasers, design computer chips, invent new materials, and even try to build quantum computers. This lesson gives a snapshot of the kinds of projects, careers, and communities built around this field.",
      "title": "What people do with quantum ideas"
    },
    {
      "description": "This lesson previews how the full course will guide you from basic concepts toward the actual tools physicists use, so you can see the path ahead and know what kind of understanding you're building toward.",
      "title": "Where this course will take you next"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "chapter": {
    "description": "Before diving into rules and case law, take a quick look at what civil procedure actually is: the rulebook that decides how lawsuits move from a complaint to a courtroom to a final judgment. This chapter shows why these rules shape everything from small disputes to massive corporate battles, and why understanding them changes how you see the legal system.",
    "title": "What civil procedure is and why it matters"
  },
  "lessons": [
    {
      "description": "Civil procedure sets the rules for how private disputes get resolved in court, from filing a complaint to enforcing a final judgment. See how it acts as the invisible skeleton holding every lawsuit together, no matter what the case is actually about.",
      "title": "The rulebook behind every lawsuit"
    },
    {
      "description": "A single missed deadline or wrong filing can end a case before anyone argues the actual facts. Discover why procedure often matters more than who is 'right,' and how small technical choices can decide big outcomes.",
      "title": "How a deadline can decide a case"
    },
    {
      "description": "From consumer class actions to neighbor disputes, procedural rules quietly shape who can sue, where, and how much it costs. See real situations where these rules affect ordinary people, not just big corporations.",
      "title": "Where procedure shows up in real disputes"
    },
    {
      "description": "Litigators, judges, clerks, and mediators all rely on procedural strategy to move cases forward or shut them down early. Get a glimpse of the roles and everyday decisions built entirely around these rules.",
      "title": "Who uses these rules every day"
    },
    {
      "description": "This course walks through the life of a lawsuit step by step, from jurisdiction to appeal, using real rules and cases. See how each chapter builds the toolkit you'll use to read, argue, and think like someone fluent in courtroom mechanics.",
      "title": "What this course will walk you through"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "chapter": {
    "description": "Antes de entrar de lleno al curso, esta primera parada te muestra qué es el urbanismo desde afuera: cómo mira las ciudades, por qué las decisiones sobre calles y edificios afectan tu vida diaria, y qué caminos existen para quienes se apasionan por diseñar mejores lugares para vivir.",
    "title": "Un primer vistazo al urbanismo"
  },
  "lessons": [
    {
      "description": "Por qué las ciudades no crecen al azar: alguien decide dónde va un parque, qué tan anchas son las calles y dónde se ponen las paradas de autobús. El urbanismo estudia esas decisiones y sus efectos en la vida real.",
      "title": "Qué estudia el urbanismo"
    },
    {
      "description": "Una calle angosta con árboles puede sentirse más segura que una avenida ancha y vacía. Descubre cómo pequeños detalles del diseño urbano cambian por completo cómo nos sentimos y comportamos en un lugar.",
      "title": "Una idea sorprendente: el diseño cambia el comportamiento"
    },
    {
      "description": "Desde el tiempo que tardas en llegar al trabajo hasta dónde juegan los niños del barrio, el urbanismo está detrás de casi todo lo que haces afuera de tu casa, aunque casi nunca lo notes.",
      "title": "El urbanismo en tu rutina diaria"
    },
    {
      "description": "Quienes trabajan en urbanismo diseñan parques, planean transporte, negocian con vecinos o imaginan cómo será una ciudad en veinte años. Conoce algunos roles reales detrás de las ciudades que habitamos.",
      "title": "Quiénes le dan forma a las ciudades"
    },
    {
      "description": "Este curso te llevará paso a paso por las ideas, herramientas y ejemplos que usan los urbanistas para pensar espacios, calles y comunidades con más criterio y curiosidad.",
      "title": "Qué encontrarás en este curso"
    }
  ]
}

